								<p>
									Mímir is no longer just a thesis about what AI coding tools are missing. The world-state substrate is implemented, the brokered interface layer is real, and the system has been exercised across real repositories. In proving, brokered orientation emerged as the practical operating mode: the system is usually finding the right place to begin, and the remaining misses come from how and when it should widen or abstain under policy constraints.
								</p>
